{
  "title": "bigcompute: GPU-Accelerated Computational Mathematics",
  "description": "GPU-accelerated infrastructure for exploring open conjectures in number theory and combinatorics. Custom CUDA kernels for Zaremba's conjecture (210B verified), Ramsey R(5,5) (656/656 UNSAT), Kronecker coefficients (S30 26.4B triples, S40 character table), class numbers (30B discriminants), Hausdorff dimension spectra (all 2^20-1 subsets), and Ramanujan Machine formula discovery. Includes multi-model AI peer review infrastructure (41 reviews from 4 models), autonomous research agent, and distributed Colab compute notebooks. All results published at bigcompute.science.",
